attributes.Long form description: The student begins by changing the joy controllers to the comfort grip, when he finishes the student waits for new instructions. The instructor tells that he need no change the comfort grip to the joycon strap after that the student placed back the joycons on the Nintendo Switch and stand it using the kickstand, then he exchanged de game cartridge and the SD card to finally turn on and off the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: We will perform the task Nintendo switch. We will start from the handheld mode.  Uh, your first task is to change the controller from handheld mode to the joy-con comfort grip mode.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the handheld grip mode to the comfort grip mode.

attributes.Transcription: Your next task is to change from the comfort grip to the two joy-cons, two individual joy-cons.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the comfort grip to the individual joy-con controllers.

attributes.Transcription: Please lock the two joy-cons using the white button.

attributes.Action sentence: The student locks the joy-con controller strap to the joy-con.

attributes.Transcription: Your next task is to change back the the the GoPro, from the two Joy-con mode to the handheld mode.

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes from the two Joy-con mode to the handheld mode.

attributes.Transcription: Your next task is to open the kickstand of the Nintendo.

attributes.Action sentence: The student opens the kickstand of the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Transcription: The kickstand is the first thing you try to open.

attributes.Action sentence: The students closes the kickstand of the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Transcription: You can close it again. And your next task is to change the game cartridge.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the game card of the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Transcription: Your next task is to change the micro SD card.

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes the micro SD card of the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Transcription: In order to change the micro SD card, you can open carefully the kickstand. Your next task is to turn on the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns on the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Transcription: Your last task is to turn off the Nintendo switch completely.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns off the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Transcription: Your task is over and you can stop recording.
